==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''sub'' under + way

===Noun===
'''subway'''

#(''North American'') [[underground]] [[railway]].
#('''New York City, New York, USA''') The proper name of the [[Heavy Rail]] [[transit]] system - regardless of elevation.
#('''Newark, New Jersey, USA''') The proper name of the [[Light Rail]] transit system
#(''British'') underground walkway, [[tunnel]] for [[pedestrian]]s. (In the USA, this definition applies to [[Pedestrian Underpass]].)

